tholicworldvo00fathgoog#page/n742/mode/2up \"Human Nature and the Historian,\"] ''The Catholic World,'' Vol. CIV, No. 624, March 1917.\n* [https://www.jstor.org/stable/25121715 \"The Plan for a New War,\"] ''The North American Review,'' Vol. 206, No. 745, Dec. 1917.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/hibbertjournal16londuoft#page/376/mode/2up \"Stopford Brooke,\"] ''The Hibbert Journal,'' Vol. XVI, 1917/1918.\n* [https://www.jstor.org/stable/25121805 \"Germany and Alsace-Lorraine: How to Help Annexation,\"] ''The North American Review,'' Vol. 207, No. 748, Mar. 1918.\n* [https://www.jstor.org/stable/25121845 \"The Real Secret Diplomacy,\"] ''The North American Review,'' Vol. 207, No. 749, Apr. 1918.\n* [https://www.jstor.org/stable/20561825 \"A Note on the New Martyrdom,\"] ''The Lotus Magazine,'' Vol. 10, No. 2, Feb. 1919.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/LivingAge-1919mar01-00546 \"On Newspaper Proprietors,\"] ''The Living Age,'' March 1919.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/LivingAge-1919may10-00356 \"The Heretic and the Home Visitor,\"] ''The Living Age,'' May 1919.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/LivingAge-1919jul12-00081 \"Mr. Shaw and the Danger of Living,\"] ''The Living Age,'' July 1919.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/LivingAge-1919sep13-00647 \"The True Case Against Bolshevism,\"] ''The Living Age,'' September 1919.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/catholictruthinh00belluoft#page/8/mode/2up \"Anti-Catholic History.\"] In: ''Catholic and Anti-Catholic History,'' The America Press, 1920.\n* [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015032024203;view=1up;seq=47 \"The New Renascence, I: The Same Old Game,\"] ''Vanity Fair,'' January 1920.\n* [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015032024203;view=1up;seq=191 \"The New Renascence, II: The Machine of Tomfoolery,\"] ''Vanity Fair,'' Vol. 13, No. 5, February 1920.\n* [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015032024203;view=1up;seq=311 \"The New Renascence, III: Public Laws and Public Liquors,\"] ''Vanity Fair,'' March 1920.\n