9567 | archive-date = 2012-01-25 | url-status = dead }}</ref> || Curtain || As a storm thunders up the coast to Lovecraft, Massachusetts, the Keepers of the Keys face Dodge a final time, under three hundred feet of stone, in the darkness before the Black Door. Here, water will mix with blood and The Drowning Cave will become a colossal grave, in the final issue of the CLOCKWORKS storyline.\n|-\n|}\n\n===''Alpha & Omega''===\nThe final arc is titled ''Locke & Key: Alpha & Omega'', and collects ''Omega'' #1\u20135, and ''Alpha'' #1\u20132.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=joe_hill|author=Joe Hill|number=342378985679884288|date=5 June 2013|title=Yes, the final hardcover is titled LOCKE &amp; KEY: ALPHA &amp; OMEGA. All 7 issues (Omega 1 - 5, Alpha 1 &amp;2) will be included.}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 80px;\"|'''Issue''' !! '''Release''' !! '''Chapter Title''' !! '''Summary'''\n|-\n| ''' ''Omega'' #1''' || November 14, 2012 || Our Regrets || The beginning of the end starts here. Dodge has the Omega key, and nothing can stop him from using it...\n|-\n| ''' ''Omega'' #2''' || December 19, 2012 || The Soldier || A ghost haunts the long halls of Keyhouse\u2014the spirit of Bode Locke, cast out of his body by the Demon named Dodge\u2014and only one person can hear his voice: Bode's old playmate, Rufus Whedon.<ref>[http://www.legionofcomics.co.uk/acatalog/LOCKE___KEY_OMEGA__2.html Legionofcomics.co.uk]{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|-\n| ''' ''Omega'' #3''' || February 20, 2013 || Last Dance || As Kinsey Locke and the other students head to a dance at Lovecraft Academy, the demonic Dodge gathers shadowy forces of his own and enacts his evil endgame. The \u201cLast Dance\u201d begins here.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.inter-comics.com/shop/locke-key-omega-3-of-7 |title=Inter-comics.com |access-date=2012-12-11 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130127025453/https://www.inter-comics.com/shop/locke-key-omega-3-of-7 |archive-date=2013-01-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| ''' ''Omega'' #4''' || April 3, 2013 || Human Sacrifices|| The bottomless pit of the Drowning Cave threatens to become a mass grave, as Dodge springs a fatal trap on the senior class of Lovecraft Academy. Hope is as fragile as a candle-flame wavering in the night. . . and as easy to extinguish.\n|-\n| ''' ''Omega'' #5''' || June 5, 2013 || The Fall || In the Drowning Cave, the black door is open at last, and for the kids trapped down there, the choice is simple: resist and die, or pass through the door and be lost forever. In the hole beneath Keyhouse the stones run with blood, the living shadows run riot, and time runs out... as ''Locke & Key'' enters its final chapters.\n|-\n| ''' ''Alpha'' #1'''<ref>{{cite web|last=Phegley|first=Kiel|title=C2E2: New Books Make Waves at Diamond Summit|url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=45138|publisher=Comic Book Resources|accessdate=27 April 2013}}</ref> || September 11, 2013<ref>{{cite tweet|user=IDWPublishing|author=IDW Publishing|number=372761461451276289|date=28 August 2013|title=Locke &amp; Key: Alpha #1 will be out on 9/11/13. Sorry for the delay, but this is one that couldn't be rushed. Perfection takes time.}}</ref> || Alpha ||In the penultimate issue of ''Locke & Key'', the damned and the saved alike will make their final stand in the Drowning Cave, in a clash of blood and fire. The shadows have never been darker and the end has never been closer. Turn the key and open the last door; it's time to say goodbye.<ref>[http://www.previewsworld.com/Home/1/1/71/916?stockItemID=JUN130329 Previewsworld.com]</ref>\n|-\n| ''' ''Alpha'' #2''' ||December 18, 2013<ref name=\"Ryallsfiles\">[http://ryallsfiles.tumblr.com/post/66916898702/advance-copies-of-the-final-issue-of-locke-key Ryallsfiles]</ref>|| The Last Door ||\"The End.\" A door claps softly shut. A key scrapes in a last rusted lock. It ends here: the story of the Locke children and their desperate, tragic battle with the monster set on destroying them... the past.<ref name=\"previewsworld.com\">[http://www.previewsworld.com/Home/1/1/71/916?stockItemID=AUG130400 Previewsworld.com]</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===''World War Key''===\nAt the 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]], Joe Hill confirmed that a new ''Locke & Key'' series called ''World War Key'' was in the works.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/horror/2019/08/18/locke-and-key-new-comics-netflix-series-joe-hill-world-war-key/|title=Locke & Key Creators Confirm More Comics Are on the Way|last=Lovett|first=Jamie|date=August 18, 2019|website=comicbook.com}}</ref> This storyline as Hill puts it is ''\"about the idea that the past is never gone... and I think a lot of ghost stories are about ways the past keep bleeding through to the present. We'll visit the [[American Revolutionary War|Revolutionary War]], [[American Civil War|Civil War]], and [[World War II]] to show how those past events have had lingering effects on our heroes today.\"''<ref name=\":1\" /> As of 2019, the series is expected to run thirty-seven issues across six books (not including ''The Golden Age'').<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hill |first1=Joe |last2=Rodriguez |first2=Gabriel |title=Locke & Key: Small World |publisher=IDW |location=Interview: \"A Conversation about Locke & Key\"}}</ref> ''World War Key'' is designed to be both a prequel and a sequel to the original run of ''Locke & Key''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Skye |first1=Louis |title=10 Years of Locke and Key: The Creators on the Journey So Far |url=https://womenwriteaboutcomics.com/2018/04/10-years-of-locke-and-key-the-creators-on-the-journey-so-far/ |accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====''The Golden Age''====\nA series of short stories set in the past.<ref>{{cite news|last=Truitt|first=Brian|title=Joe Hill hopes to \"stick the landing\" for \"Locke & Key\"|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/2012/11/13/joe-hill-locke-key-omega-comic-book-series/1702663/|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=21 April 2013|date=November 13, 2012}}</ref> In his newsletter, Joe Hill referred to the book as \"''World War Key 0: The Golden Age''\".<ref name=\"EH037\">{{cite web |last1=Hill |first1=Joe |title=Escape Hatch 037: Ride On |url=https://mailchi.mp/joehillfiction/escape-hatch-037-ride-on?e=a00c7b5aaf |accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n''Locke & Key: In Pale Battalions Go'' will be a two-issue story that leads into ''World War Key'', set at the beginning of the 20th century and will feature characters from \"Small World\" and \"Open the Moon\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Locke & Key's Next Comic Will Be a 'Gateway to a Larger Story' |url=https://www.cbr.com/locke-key-battalions-one-shot-announced/ |website=cbr.co |publisher=cbr.com}}</ref> It will also lead into the ''Locke & Key/Sandman Universe'' crossover comic.<ref name=\"EH037\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 190px;\"|'''Issue''' !! '''Release''' !! '''Summary'''\n|-\n| '''''Guide to the Known Keys''''' || November 23, 2011 || This special standalone issue features an expanded \"Guide to the Known Keys\", an all-new \"Guide to Failed Keys\", and a story of summer night magic titled \"Open the Moon\", set in Keyhouse's unlikely past.\n|-\n| '''''Grindhouse''''' || August 29, 2012 || Set in the glare of a Depression-era summer, in which three Canuck gangsters carry out a heist and hide out at the Keyhouse. ''Locke & Key: Grindhouse'' includes an expanded \"Guide to Keyhouse\" describing the mansion.\n|-\n| '''''Small World''''' || December 21, 2016 || An impossible birthday gift for two little girls unexpectedly throws open a door to a monster on eight legs. Joe Hill has said that the title is a shout out to the horror novel of the same name by his mother [[Tabitha King]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Johnston|first=Rich|title=A Locke & Key Christmas Miracle From Joe Hill And Gabriel Rodriguez|url=http://www.bleedingcool.com/2016/06/15/a-locke-key-christmas-miracle-from-joe-hill-and-gabriel-rodriguez/|publisher=Bleeding Cool Comic Book, Movie, TV News|accessdate=June 15, 2016|date=June 15, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''''Nailed It''''' || July 19, 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsarama.com/45936-idw-rolls-out-sdcc-plans-as-it-celebrates-its-20th-comic-con.html|title=IDW Rolls Out SDCC Plans as It Celebrates Its 20th Comic-Con|last=Staff|first=Newsarama|date=July 9, 2019|website=Newsarama|access-date=July 30, 2019}}</ref> || A 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]] Exclusive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.idwpublishing.com/idw-announces-signing-schedule-panels-and-exclusives-for-san-diego-comic-con-international-2019/|title=IDW Announces Signing Schedule, Panels, and Exclusives for San Diego Comic-Con International 2019|last=Publishing|first=IDW|date=July 9, 2019|website=IDW Publishing|access-date=July 30, 2019}}</ref> \"Some doors, once closed, can never be opened again. While others shouldn\u2019t be reopened ever again\u2026\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2019/07/29/locke-key-namejoe-hill-martin-simmonds/|title=Locke & Key Changes Name, New Series by Joe Hill and Martin Simmonds to be Previewed|last=Johnston|first=Rich|date=July 29, 2019|website=Bleeding Cool|access-date=July 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''''Dog Days''''' || November 6, 2019 || A 48-page special containing \"Dog Days\" and recollecting \"Nailed It\" in one issue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://icv2.com/articles/news/view/43742/joe-hill-gabriel-rodriguez-return-locke-key|title=JOE HILL AND GABRIEL RODRIGUEZ RETURN TO 'LOCKE & KEY'|last=Alverson|first=Brigid|date=August 1, 2019|website=ICv2|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=September 10, 2019}}</ref> Two boys of the Locke family use the Animal Key to turn their pet dog into a human boy.\n|-\n|'''''In Pale Battalions Go'' #1'''<ref name=\"Cover 1 reveal\">{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GR_comics/status/1249121481369534467|title=Gabriel Rodriguez Twitter|last=Rodriguez|first=Gabriel|date=April 11, 2020|website=Twitter|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> || 2020 || TBA\n|-\n|'''''In Pale Battalions Go'' #2''' || 2020 || TBA\n|}\n\n====Revolution====\nThe first arc of ''World War Key''.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n!'''Issue''' !! '''Release''' !! '''Chapter Title''' !! '''Summary'''\n|-\n|'''#1''' ||2020<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/joehill/comments/cgxket/more_locke_and_key_coming_in_2020_image_from_the/|title=More Locke and Key coming in 2020 (image from the SDCC \u201cNailed It\u201d comic)|last=Kwyjibo331|first=u/|date=July 23, 2019|website=Reddit|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 2, 2019}}</ref> || TBD || TBD\n|}\n\n===\"Hell & Gone\"===\nOn February 21st 2020 IDW announced via their twitter<ref>{{cite web |title=LOCKE & KEY: HELL & GONE - A SANDMAN UNIVERSE Crossover Event |url=https://twitter.com/IDWPublishing/status/1231017077890277376?ref_src=twsrc^tfw |website=twitter.com |publisher=IDW Publishing}}</ref> that ''Locke & Key'' would be crossing over with [[DC Comics]]'s ''[[The Sandman Universe|Sandman Universe]]'', the story will center around DC's Key to Hell from ''The Sandman'' story arc \"Season of Mists\".\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n!'''Issue''' !! '''Release''' !! '''Chapter Title''' !! '''Summary'''\n|-\n| '''#1''' || October 2020 || TBD|| TBD\n|}\n\n==Collected editions==\n\n===Standard editions===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!'''Volume''' !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 130px;\"|'''Release''' !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 140px;\"|'''Title''' !! '''Summary''' !!scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 190px;\"| '''ISBN'''\n|-\n| '''1''' || October 8, 2008 || ''Locke & Key<br />Welcome to Lovecraft'' || Collects ''Welcome to Lovecraft'' #1\u20136 || {{ISBNT|9781600102370}} (Hardcover)<br />{{ISBNT|9781600103841}} (Paperback)\n|-\n| '''2''' || September 30, 2009 || ''Locke & Key<br />Head Games ''|| Collects ''Head Games'' #1\u20136 || {{ISBNT|9781600104831}} (Hardcover)<br />{{ISBNT|9781600107610}} (Paperback)\n|-\n| '''3''' || July 29, 2010 || ''Locke & Key<br />Crown of Shadows'' || Collects ''Crown of Shadows'' #1\u20136 || {{ISBNT|9781600106958}} (Hardcover)<br />{{ISBNT|9781600109539}} (Paperback)\n|-\n| '''4''' || July 19, 2011 || ''Locke & Key<br />Keys to the Kingdom ''|| Collects ''Keys to the Kingdom'' #1\u20136 || {{ISBNT|9781600108860}} (Hardcover)<br />{{ISBNT|9781613772072}} (Paperback)\n|-\n| '''5''' || July 24, 2012 || ''Locke & Key<br />Clockworks'' || Collects ''Clockworks'' #1\u20136 || {{ISBNT|9781613772270}} (Hardcover)<br />{{ISBNT|9781613776995}} (Paperback)\n|-\n| '''6''' || February 4, 2014 || ''Locke & Key<br />Alpha & Omega'' || Collects ''Omega'' #1\u20135 and ''Alpha'' #1\u20132 || {{ISBNT|9781613778531}} (Hardcover)<br />{{ISBNT|9781631401442}} (Paperback)\n|-\n| '''\u2014''' || January 4, 2017 || ''Locke & Key<br />Small World''<ref>{{cite news|title=Locke & Key: Small World (Preview)|url=http://www.cbr.com/locke-key-small-world/|publisher=[[Comic Book Resources]]|accessdate=September 12, 2017|date=December 20, 2016}}</ref> || Collects ''The Golden Age'' stand-alone issue ''Small World''. || {{ISBNT|9781631408465}} (Hardcover)\n|-\n| '''\u2014''' || August 15, 2017 || ''Locke & Key<br />Heaven and Earth''<ref>{{cite news|last=Ching|first=Albert|title=Rare Locke & Key One-Shots Collected In New Hardcover|url=http://www.cbr.com/locke-and-key-heaven-and-earth-hardcover/|publisher=[[Comic Book Resources]]|accessdate=April 17, 2017|date=April 12, 2017}}</ref> || Collects ''The Golden Age'' stand-alone short stories \"Open the Moon\", ''Grindhouse'', and \"In the Can\", (a rare ''Locke and Key'' short that was published in ''IDW: 10 Year Anniversary Comic Book'' in 2009) || {{ISBNT|9781684051816}} (Hardcover)\n|}\n\nOn November 11, 2014, the first six volumes were collected as a slipcase set of paperbacks.\n\n===Master editions===\n''Locke & Key'' was also collected in three hardcover books with all-new cover art and design by Gabriel Rodriguez.\n* '''''Locke & Key Master Edition Volume 1''''' (May 19, 2015). Collects the first two arcs, ''Welcome to Lovecraft'' and ''Head Games''.\n* '''''Locke & Key Master Edition Volume 2''''' (March 22, 2016). Collects the third and fourth arcs, ''Crown of Shadows'' and ''Keys to the Kingdom''.\n* '''''Locke & Key Master Edition Volume 3''''' (October 18, 2016). Collects the fifth and sixth arcs, ''Clockworks'' and ''Alpha & Omega''.\n\n===Signed limited editions===\nOn November 11, 2007, [[Subterranean Press]] announced a pre-order for a hand-numbered, signed, limited edition of the six-issue run of ''Welcome To Lovecraft''. This edition consisted of 250 numbered copies and 26 lettered copies, both of which sold out within 24 hours of being announced.<ref>{{cite web| title = Teaser \u2014 Locke & Key by Joe Hill| publisher = [[Subterranean Press]]| date = 2007-11-11| url = http://subterraneanpress.com/index.php/2007/11/11/teaser-locke-key-by-joe-hill/| accessdate = 2008-12-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title = Limited and Lettered LOCKE & KEY by Joe Hill Sold Out| publisher = [[Subterranean Press]]| date = 2007-11-24| url = http://subterraneanpress.com/index.php/2007/11/24/limited-and-lettered-locke-key-by-joe-hill-sold-out/| accessdate = 2008-12-09| url-status = dead| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080820155436/http://subterraneanpress.com/index.php/2007/11/24/limited-and-lettered-locke-key-by-joe-hill-sold-out| archivedate = 2008-08-20}}</ref> This edition was a hardcover release in a specially designed and illustrated slipcase, and featured exclusive dust jacket art by [[Vincent Chong]] and reprinted all 250 pages of [[Joe Hill (writer)|Joe Hill]]'s script in addition to the actual comic work.<ref>{{cite web| title = Joe Hill \u2014 LOCKE & KEY Update| publisher = [[Subterranean Press]]| date = 2008-06-07| url = http://subterraneanpress.com/index.php/2008/06/07/joe-hill-locke-key-update/| accessdate = 2008-12-09}}</ref>\n\nThis was followed by the publication of ''Head Games'', which was also limited to 250 hand-numbered and signed copies as well as 26 lettered copies.<ref>{{cite web| title = Joe Hill \u2014 discovered an amazing singer tamia d. holder who will soon be working tour with mindless behavior and more she will be the n.b.t out there for single song writer already has 2 songs of her own.| publisher = [[Subterranean Press]]| date = 2009-04-27| url = http://subterraneanpress.com/index.php/2009/04/27/joe-hill-head-games-is-coming-to-subterranean/| accessdate = 2011-02-12}}</ref>\nThe third volume, ''Crown of Shadows'', is available for preorder, and like the previous editions is signed and numbered with the same limitations and also comes with an illustrated slipcase.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://subterraneanpress.com/store/product_detail/locke_key_crown_of_shadows |title=Subterraneanpress.com |access-date=2013-01-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130117074554/http://subterraneanpress.com/store/product_detail/locke_key_crown_of_shadows |archive-date=2013-01-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nCloth-bound trade editions limited to 1000 copies (unsigned, unnumbered, and without the slipcase) were also released. Trade editions for the first two volumes are sold out.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\nAt the 2009 [[Eisner Awards]], ''Locke & Key'' was nominated for Best Limited Series and Joe Hill was nominated for Best Writer.{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}\n\nIt won the 2009 [[British Fantasy Award]] for Best Comic or Graphic Novel.{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}\n\nIt won the 2011 Eisner Award for Best Writer (Joe Hill), and was nominated for Best Single Issue, Best Continuing Series, and Best Penciller.\n\nIt won the 2012 [[British Fantasy Award]] for Best Comic or Graphic Novel.<ref>{{cite web|title=British Fantasy Awards 2012|url=http://www.britishfantasysociety.co.uk/news/british-fantasy-awards-2012/|work=yes|publisher=British Fantasy Society|accessdate=4 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Adaptations==\n\n===Film===\nA film trilogy was officially announced at the 2014 Comic Con. [[Alex Kurtzman]], [[Roberto Orci]], [[Bobby Cohen]] and Ted Adams would produce the film with [[Universal Pictures]] and Kurtzman and Orci's production company [[K/O Paper Products]].<ref>Kit, Borys (June 19, 2013). [http://hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/universal-picks-up-locke-key-571840 \"Universal Picks Up 'Locke & Key' Comic\"]. ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]''.</ref>\n\nIn October 2015, Joe Hill confirmed that the films are no longer happening. However, he stated that TV series is still possible.<ref>DiVincenzo, Alex (October 5, 2015). [http://brokehorrorfan.com/post/130564700528/i-had-the-pleasure-of-meeting-author-joe-hill-at-a \"Locke & Key Film Adaptation Dead, TV Series Still Possible\"]. ''Broke Horror Fan''.</ref> In May 2016, Joe Hill announced he would write a TV pilot, serve as executive producer and pitch the show to various networks and streaming companies.<ref>Goncalves, Sarah (May 2016). [http://screenrant.com/locke-key-tv-show-joe-hill/ \"Locke & Key TV Series With Joe Hill Moving Forward\"].</ref>\n\n===Television===\n\n====Fox pilot (2010\u20132011)====\n{{see also|Locke & Key (TV pilot)}}\n\n[[Dimension Films]] acquired the film and television rights for ''Welcome to Lovecraft'' from [[IDW Publishing]] with the intent of developing the property as a feature with [[John Davis (producer)|John Davis]] producing.<ref>[http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/18977 Dimension Loses Rights to Joe Hill's Awesome 'Locke & Key' Comic!]</ref> In February 2010, it was announced that Dimension had lost the adaptation rights to Dreamworks<ref>[http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/35715/dreamworks-keeping-newly-acquired-property-under-locke-key DreamWorks Keeping Newly Acquired Property Under Locke & Key]</ref> with [[Alex Kurtzman]] and [[Roberto Orci]] signed on to develop and produce the project.<ref>[http://www.latinoreview.com/news/exclusive-kurtzman-orci-to-produce-locke-key-9138 Exclusive: Kurtzman & Orci To Produce Locke & Key]</ref> In August 2010 [[Steven Spielberg]] also joined as a producer, and the production became a TV series rather than a movie adaptation, with [[Josh Friedman]] writing episodes for the show and acting as show-runner.<ref>[http://leagueofcomicgeeks.com/news/335/locke-and-key-adaptation-becomes-tv-series Locke & Key Adaptation Becomes TV Series]</ref>\n\nThe TV series adaptation then landed at [[20th Century Fox Television]]. The network greenlit a [[pilot episode|pilot]], produced by [[Dreamworks TV]] and [[K/O Paper Products]] through the latter's deal with 20th Century Fox TV.<ref>{{cite news|first=Michael|last=Schneider|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118026326.html?categoryid=14&cs=1|title=Fox greenlights 'Locke and Key'|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=2010-10-25|accessdate=2010-10-26}}</ref>\n\n[[Miranda Otto]] played Nina Locke, [[Sarah Bolger]] was Kinsey Locke<ref>{{Cite news|first=Scott|last=Tady|title=Pilot for new TV show show in Pittsburgh|date=2010-11-26 |newspaper=[[Beaver County Times]]|url=http://www.timesonline.com/bct_news/news_details/article/1373/2010/november/26/pilot-for-new-tv-show-show-in-pittsburgh.html| accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Cathy|last=Hayes|title=Irish Sarah Bolger cast in Fox\u2019s 'Locke & Key'|date=2010-12-20|publisher=IrishCentral|url= http://www.irishcentral.com/ent/Irish-Sarah-Bolger-cast-in-Foxs-Locke--Key-112181554.html|accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref> and [[Nick Stahl]] co-starred as Duncan Locke.<ref>{{cite web|first=Josh|last=Wigler|url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2011/01/13/nick-stahl-joins-locke-key-fox-targets-fall-premiere/|title=Nick Stahl Joins 'Locke & Key,' FOX Targets Fall Premiere|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=2011-01-13|accessdate=2011-01-19}}</ref> Skylar Gaertner played 6-year old Bode, and Harrison Thomas played a teenager possessed by an evil spirit.<ref>{{cite web |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |url=http://www.deadline.com/2011/01/bones-spinoff-the-finder-finds-lead/ |title='Bones' Spinoff 'The Finder' Finds Lead |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=January 28, 2011 |accessdate=February 4, 2011 }}</ref> Actor and singer [[Jesse McCartney]] appeared as Ty Locke, the series' male lead<ref>{{cite web |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |url=http://www.deadline.com/2011/02/jesse-mccartney-to-star-in-foxs-lock-key/ |title=Jesse McCartney To Star In 'Locke & Key' |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=February 3, 2011 |accessdate=February 4, 2011 }}</ref> and [[Ksenia Solo]] was cast as Dodge.<ref>{{cite web |first=Kevin |last=Melrose |url=http://spinoff.comicbookresources.com/2011/02/21/foxs-locke-key-finds-its-dodge/ |title=Fox\u2019s Locke & Key Finds Its Dodge |publisher= |date=February 21, 2011 |accessdate=February 21, 2011 }}</ref>\n\n[[Mark Romanek]] directed the pilot episode,<ref>{{cite web |first=Jeff |last=Leins |url=http://www.newsinfilm.com/2010/11/23/mark-romanek-to-direct-locke-key-tv-pilot/ |title=Mark Romanek to Direct 'Locke & Key' TV Pilot |work=News in Film |date=November 23, 2010 |access-date=November 24, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120603170819/http://www.newsinfilm.com/2010/11/23/mark-romanek-to-direct-locke-key-tv-pilot/ |archive-date=June 3, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> which was filmed at the mansion in [[Hartwood Acres]] and in [[Ellwood City, Pennsylvania]], in February 2011. The pilot was also shot throughout [[Pittsburgh]] that same month.<ref>{{cite news |first=Rob |last=Owen |url=http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/11042/1124560-67.stm/ |title=Tuned In: Fox pilot 'Locke & Key' filming in Pittsburgh |publisher= post-gazette.com |date=February 11, 2011 |accessdate=February 21, 2011 }}</ref> In May 2011, Fox announced that the project would not be picked up to the series.<ref>{{cite news|last=Owen|first=Rob|title=Fox reportedly passes on 'Locke & Key'|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/11131/1145721-100.stm|accessdate=11 May 2011|newspaper=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|date=11 May 2011}}</ref> The studio attempted to sell the project to other networks but eventually ceased efforts due to rising costs. The pilot was screened at the 2011 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]], where it was well received.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|url=http://www.deadline.com/2011/06/fox-pilot-locke-key-to-screen-at-comic-con/|title=Fox Pilot 'Locke & Key' To Screen At Comic-Con |website=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 22, 2011|accessdate=June 22, 2011}}</ref>\n\n====Hulu pilot (2017\u20132018)====\n\nOn April 20, 2017, [[Hulu]] ordered a pilot based on the comic with [[Carlton Cuse]], [[Scott Derrickson]], and Lindsey Springer as producers.<ref>{{cite web|first=Daniel|last=Holloway|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/hulu-carlton-cuse-1202391596/|title=Hulu Orders Carlton Cuse Pilot \u2018Locke and Key\u2019|publisher=Variety|date=April 20, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> In July 2017, Derrickson was replaced by [[Andy Muschietti]] as the pilot's director.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|url=http://deadline.com/2017/07/locke-key-andy-muschietti-replace-scott-derrickson-director-hulu-pilot-1202129058/|title=\u2018Locke and Key\u2019: Andy Muschietti To Direct Hulu Pilot Based On Graphic Novel|date=14 July 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=17 August 2017}}</ref> In August 2017, [[Frances O'Connor]] was cast as Nina in the show.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/locke-key-frances-oconnor-cast-star-hulu-pilot-carlton-cuse-joe-hill-1202150760/|title=\u2018Locke and Key\u2019: Frances O\u2019Connor To Star In Hulu Pilot From Carlton Cuse & Joe Hill|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=14 July 2017}}</ref> In a March 2018 interview, Samantha Mathis revealed that Hulu had passed on the show, and it was now being shopped around to other networks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://culturedvultures.com/sxsw-2018-logan-miller-samantha-mathis-talk-you-can-choose-your-family/|title=SXSW 2018: Logan Miller & Samantha Mathis Talk You Can Choose Your Family|date=2018-03-23|work=Cultured Vultures|access-date=2018-04-04|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n====Netflix series (2020)====\n{{see also|Locke & Key (TV series)}}\n\nOn May 30, 2018, after Hulu had passed on ''Locke & Key'', it was announced that [[Netflix]] was nearing a series order for a re-developed version of the show with Cuse and Hill involved once again, and Muschietti as executive producer. The show found a new director for the pilot and an entirely new cast with the exception of [[Jackson Robert Scott]] as Bode Locke, who was cast in the Hulu pilot as well.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/locke-key-drama-from-carlton-cuse-joe-hill-close-to-series-order-at-netflix-1202398905/|title=\u2018Locke & Key\u2019 Drama From Carlton Cuse & Joe Hill Nears Series Order At Netflix|website=Deadline|date=29 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nSeason one of the show, with 10 episodes, debuted on Netflix on February 7th, 2020.\n\n===Audio drama===\nAll six books of ''Locke & Key'' were adapted as a 13-hour [[audio drama]] released on 5 October 2015. Produced by the [[AudioComics Company]] for [[Audible.com|Audible]] Studios and directed by William Dufris, the work features the voices of [[Tatiana Maslany]], [[Haley Joel Osment]], [[Kate Mulgrew]], with appearances by Hill, Rodr\u00edguez, and [[Stephen King]] in addition to almost 50 voice-over actors<ref>{{cite web|last=Zalben|first=Alex|title='Locke & Key' Is Coming Back \u2014 With Tatiana Maslany And An All-Star Cast|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2199716/locke-and-key-audio-book-audible/|date=7 July 2015|publisher=MTV|accessdate=13 August 2015}}</ref> and an original score by Peter Van Riet. The work received critical praise, and in 2016 was nominated for four Audie Awards from the Audiobook Publisher's Association of America, including \"Best Original Work\" and \"Excellence in Production.\"\n\n===Card game===\nIn 2012, Cryptozoic Entertainment released a card game based on the series.<ref>{{cite web|last=Moore|first=Debi|title=''Locke & Key: The Game Now Available from Cryptozoic Entertainment''|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/31176/locke-key-the-game-now-available-from-cryptozoic-entertainment/|date=22 February 2012|publisher=Dread Central|accessdate=13 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[The Lost Room]] - Prior work from 2006 with a very similar main concept to ''Locke & Key'', a set of magical objects with different properties including a key that opens any door to anywhere.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{gcdb series|id=29935|title=Locke & Key: Welcome to Lovecraft}}\n* {{comicbookdb|type=title|id=17073|title=''Locke & Key: Welcome to Lovecraft''}}\n* {{gcdb series|id=35508|title=Locke & Key: Head Games }}\n* {{comicbookdb|type=title|id=22187|title=''Locke & Key: Head Games ''}}\n* {{gcdb series|id=44506|title=Locke & Key: Crown of Shadows}}\n* {{comicbookdb|type=title|id=25930|title=''Locke & Key: Crown of Shadows''}}\n* {{gcdb series|id=51870|title=Locke & Key: Keys to the Kingdom}}\n* {{comicbookdb|type=title|id=30137|title=''Locke & Key: Keys to the Kingdom''}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://joehillfiction.com/?cat=8 ''Locke & Key'' section] at [[Joe Hill (writer)|Joe Hill]]'s website\n* [http://gabrielrodriguez.deviantart.com Gabriel Rodriguez's online gallery] at [[DeviantArt]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100101213343/http://idwpublishing.com/catalog/series/408 ''Locke & Key'' section] at [[IDW Publishing]]'s website\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081207000650/http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=122865 Interview with Joe Hill about the series] at [[Newsarama]]\n* [http://www.tfaw.com/blog/2009/10/26/writer-joe-hill-talks-to-tfaw-com-about-locke-key-from-idw/?qt=ea_L&Kwiki1 Writer Joe Hill Talks to TFAW.com About ''Locke & Key'' From IDW]\n* [http://www.dinova.cl/es/buscar?orderby=position&or