 =\n | pattern_b2               =\n | pattern_ra2              =\n | pattern_sh2              =\n | pattern_so2              =\n | leftarm2                 = 1845BD\n | body2                    = 1845BD\n | rightarm2                = 1845BD\n | shorts2                  = FFFFFF\n | socks2                   = 1845BD\n}}\n\n'''Accra Lions Football Club''' is a [[professional]] [[sports]] club based in [[East Legon]], [[Accra]], [[Ghana]]. The club is competing in the [[Division One League, Ghana|Division One League]], the second-tier of Ghana [[Association football|Football]] and in the [[Ghanaian FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 MTN FA Cup preliminary round fixtures|url=https://footballmadeinghana.com/2018/04/05/2018-mtn-fa-cup-preliminary-round-fixtures/|publisher=FootballMadeinGhana|accessdate=6 August 2018|date=5 April 2018}}</ref> They play their home matches at the [[Accra Sports Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Accra Lions FC opts for Accra Sports Stadium as home ground for Division One League campaign|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/accra-lions-fc-opts-for-accra-sports-stadium-as-home-ground-for-division-one-league-campaign|publisher=Ghanasoccernet|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref> [[Rainer Kraft]] is the coach of the side.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Accra Lions FC.jpg|thumb|ALFC training at the Presec Park in Legon-Accra]]\n\nAccra Lions Football Club was founded on 12 December 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Our history|url=http://www.accralions.com/club/history|publisher=Accra Lions Football Club|accessdate=9 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThey secure promotion after just two seasons in the [[Greater Accra]] [[Division Two (Ghana)|Division Two]] after winning the Zone IV division with a record 73 points in 28 matches to qualify for the middle league.<ref>{{cite web|title=Our History|url=http://www.accralions.com/club/history|publisher=Accra Lions FC|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring the [[Greater Accra]] promotional playoffs at the [[Tema Sports Stadium]], Accra Lions booked the sole qualification ticket with a 100% winning record. They beat Emmanuel FC (4-1), R-Stakes (3-0) and Photizo Future Professionals (2-0) to slot into Division One Zone III which includes clubs based in [[Greater Accra]], [[Eastern Region (Ghana)|Eastern Region]] and [[Volta Region]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Accra Lions FC snatch Greater Accra Division One League ticket with three straight wins|url=http://ghanasoccernet.com/accra-lions-fc-snatch-greater-accra-division-one-league-ticket-with-three-straight-wins|publisher=GhanaSoccernet|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 January 2018, Accra Lions officially announced the [[Accra Sports Stadium]] as their new home ground for the 2017/2018 Division One League.<ref>{{cite web|title=Accra Lions FC opts for Accra Sports Stadium as home ground for Division One League campaign|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/accra-lions-fc-opts-for-accra-sports-stadium-as-home-ground-for-division-one-league-campaign|publisher=Ghanasoccernet|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 they made their debut in the [[Division One League, Ghana|Ghana Division One]]- Zone Three<ref>{{cite web|title=Division One - Zone Three|url=https://www.ghanafa.org/division-one/division-one-zone-three|publisher=Ghana Football Association|accessdate=9 July 2018}}</ref> and in the [[Ghanaian FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=MTN FA CUP PRELIMINARY ROUND GAMES TO BE PLAYED THIS WEEKEND|url=https://www.ghanafa.org/mtn-fa-cup-preliminary-round-games-to-be-played-this-weekend|publisher=Ghana Football Association|accessdate=6 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Staff ==\n\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Accra Lions FC Staff|url=http://www.accralions.com/team/staff|publisher=Accra Lions Football Club|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n;Head coach\n* {{Flagicon|Germany}} [[Rainer Kraft]]\n\n;Team Manager:\n* {{Flagicon|Ghana}} Ishmael Hamidu\n\n;Director of Finance & Administration\n\n* {{Flagicon|Ghana}} Enoch Kofi Osei\n\n;Assistant Coach:\n* {{Flagicon|Ghana}} Nuru Yakubu\n\